org.tms.api.factories

Class TableFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.tms.api.factories.TableFactory

  • public final class TableFactory
extends java.lang.Object
    The class TableFactory contains methods to construct Table objects as well as to import data in other formats (e.g., CSV, Microsoft Excel) into Tables

    Since:
    "1.0"
    Version:
    "1.3"

    • Method Detail

      • createTable

        public static Table createTable()
        Create a new Table in the default TableContext. The new table has no Rows, Columns, or Cells, however, space is allocated based on the default parameters in the default TableContext. The new table is returned.
        Returns:
        the new Table.

      • createTable

        public static Table createTable(int nRows,
                                int nCols)
        Create a new Table in the default TableContext. The new table has no Rows, Columns, or Cells, however, space is allocated for nRows Rows and nCols Columns.
        Parameters:
        nRows - number of Rows space is allocated for
        nCols - number of Columns space is allocated for
        Returns:
        the new Table.

      • createTable

        public static Table createTable(Table template)
        Create a new Table in the default TableContext. The new table has no Rows, Columns, or Cells, however, space is allocated based on the utilization of the specified template Table.
        Parameters:
        template - Table used to initialize configurable options in the new Table
        Returns:
        the new, initialized, Table

      • fromCollection

        public static Table fromCollection(java.util.Collection<?> c)
        Creates a new Table in the default TableContext from the specified Collection c. The data in the Collection is added to the first Column in the new Table, in the natural order of the Collection.
        Parameters:
        c - the Collection
        Returns:
        the new Table

        Parameters:

        tableContext - TableContext where the new table is homed
        Returns:
        the new Table

      • fromMap

        public static Table fromMap(java.util.Map<?,?> map)
        Creates a new Table in the default TableContext from the specified Map map. The key data in the Map is added to the first Column in the new Table, in the natural order of the Map, and the value data is added to the second Column.
        Parameters:
        map - the Map
        Returns:
        the new Table
